MICHELLE Molatlou will be buried in Free State on Saturday.Her funeral service will take place at Boikhuco Old Age Home Hall in Bochabela, Mangaung, and she will be buried at Phahameng Cemetery.The former Miss Black South Africa and TV personality died of cervical cancer at the National District Hospital in Bloemfontein, Free State, on Tuesday.After news of her death broke, condolences immediately poured in from social media with people using the hashtag #RIPMichelleMolatlou.Former Muvhango actress Lerato Moloi told Daily Sun the news came as a shock.“I had no idea she was ill. I’m saddened by her death and feel especially sad for her two kids.Lerato said she became friends with Michelle at a young age but they grew apart as they got older.“She got married and had to focus on getting her life together.“I was in awe of her energy and now that I’m older, I see a lot of Michelle in me. She was always happy and I never saw her angry.”Actress Florence Masebe was one of the celebrities who took to Twitter to send her condolences.“Michelle was an amazing all-rounder,” said Florence.“She went from being crowned Miss Black South Africa to playing lead roles in SABC dramas, and later went into advertising. Michelle was always reinventing herself. What a sad loss.”A statement issued by Michelle’s family read: “Even in her last days, she would give words of wisdom to her family and friends about never giving up on life.”if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvxBqOtjlNiP27TDl_tzrLSj3HvD1KXZ0vy8C_VaiR40w6WXYMbGgqv9zfp4dxSQXBjoTkrfwtpfbTLZbFyCw1CtYP3NPbGpBgBNnIRtsdIccTIHCc-PLgEGyMCnoQ3RS0qyU8G-yTxEODXXzrXlkCEj_d0kRCV2mMNVp5SjcRPQyDj3qgOHhwNK_zfQxaiK-VcmRqi9FFxP7tspwIB24RqNjg8BxbG4JLeJVJQd3UF1B8K_fKJQbJChuIn366dH2a-S7rGa1jwpU7XKZtV-X-Xrsl2dhQJVhzvCw\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzJ4jvfhyza0oEAE